## The Five Interpretations as Signal-Prioritized Responses

Just as the schools of Chinese philosophy differed in which historical signals they prioritized, the five quantum interpretations differ in which measurement signals they prioritize:

### Copenhagen: Prioritizes Observer Knowledge Signal

```
Superposition → (measurement interaction) → Observer gains knowledge → 
State "collapses" because knowledge determines what is real from what is possible
```

**Pillar Emphasis:** 釋 (Interpretation) + 行 (Operation)—emphasizes role of knowledge in manifestation

### Many-Worlds: Prioritizes Branch Manifestation Signal

```
Superposition → (measurement interaction) → All branches instantiate → 
Observer finds themselves in one branch → All outcomes "real" across multiverse
```

**Pillar Emphasis:** 行 (Operation)—emphasizes that all possibilities actualizing across different branches

### Pilot-Wave: Prioritizes Hidden Structure Signal

```
Superposition exists, but hidden deterministic field (pilot wave) guides particle → 
Particle follows hidden trajectory through possibility space → 
Measurement reveals which trajectory was real all along
```

**Pillar Emphasis:** 構 (Structure)—emphasizes hidden structure organizing the possibilities

### Objective Collapse: Prioritizes Regime Violation Signal

```
Superposition maintained while coherence permits → 
When entanglement with environment exceeds threshold → 
Automatic collapse triggered as regime safeguard → 
Single outcome actualizes
```

**Pillar Emphasis:** 度 (Regime)—emphasizes automatic safeguard mechanisms

### Relational: Prioritizes Observer-System Coupling Signal

```
Properties only exist relative to observer-system interaction → 
No absolute superposition; only relational states → 
Measurement reveals the relational property between observer and system
```

**Pillar Emphasis:** 釋 (Interpretation)—emphasizes that meaning emerges from relationship

